news.title: Tekion leases over one lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru in expansion bid
news.para: Tekion, the innovator of the Automotive Retail Cloud® (ARC), the first and fastest cloud-native automotive retail SaaS platform, has also hired more local product and engineering talent.

news.title: M3M acquires two land parcels in Gurugram for Rs 670 crore from HSVP
news.para: One of the plots measuring 3 acres along golf course road will be developed into a 600,000 sq ft retail and office complex, while the 1.3-acre land parcel on MG Road will be developed as a retail complex spread over 180,000 sq. ft.

news.title: IL&FS puts more Mumbai properties on the block
news.para: Monetisation of these key properties, in the business district of Lower Parel and Chandivali, owned by the company and its wholly-owned subsidiaries, is expected to fetch over Rs 700 crore given the locations and size of these properties, property consultants said.

news.title: Pune: ED seeks possession of ABIL's plot in money laundering case
news.para: The ED had attached the plot, worth over Rs 4 crore (current marker worth over Rs 100 crore) last August in a money laundering case they have registered against him and on Tuesday, the adjudication authority had confirmed the attachment.

news.title: I-T department conducts searches in premises linked to Embassy Group
news.para: According to people aware of the matter, the searches have been conducted across as many as 50 offices of Embassy Group and its affiliates.

news.title: UK house prices surge 0.9% month-on-month in May: Nationwide
news.para: House prices rose by 0.9% month-on-month in May after a 0.4% rise in April, marking a 10th consecutive month of gains, Nationwide said.

news.title: Noida Authority razes over 50 illegal farmhouses on Yamuna floodplains
news.para: Noida Authority's Officer on Special Duty (Land) Prasun Dwivedi said besides Gulawali, illegal farmhouses and constructions in Tilwada village were also demolished during the operation that started at 9 am on Wednesday.

news.title: Gurugram: As flats get ready, new sectors' population could double in 18 months
news.para: There are around 90,000 flats or houses in 150 residential projects in New Gurugram areas from sectors 102 to 113, and 76 to 95 and 95A. Around 50% of these units are occupied and the remaining are likely to get occupied over the next year and a half.

news.title: Transfer duty on purchase of properties in Delhi above Rs 25 lakh hiked by 1%
news.para: The move is aimed at improving the financial health of the municipality which has been hit severely in past years especially due to Covid-19 pandemic. It is a first major decision after the three civic bodies - north, east and south - were unified last month.

news.title: Will take over nine private colonies by June 15: Gurugram civic body​
news.para: The decision was taken at a meeting, chaired by the MCG commissioner, on Tuesday, in which the representatives of these colonies were also present.

news.title: HDFC hikes lending rate by 5 basis points
news.para: "HDFC increases its Retail Prime Lending Rate (RPLR) on housing loans, on which its Adjustable Rate Home Loans (ARHL) are benchmarked, by 5 basis points, with effect from June 1, 2022," the housing finance company said in a statement.

news.title: Rs 63 crore water dues, 22 builders in Greater Noida get recovery notices
news.para: On Tuesday, Kapil Singh, a senior manager at GNIDA, told TOI that there are nearly 40,000 water connections in Greater Noida, of them water bills have not been paid by most for many years.

news.title: Migsun to complete stuck housing project in Greater Noida at Rs 700 crore cost
news.para: "We have taken a stuck project, The Hemisphere, in Greater Noida under the PMC model from Royale Golf Link. We will get a consultancy fee for completion of this project," Migsun group MD Yash Miglani said.

news.title: Assam CM distributes sanction letters to PMAY beneficiaries
news.para: The Chief Minister while disbursing the first instalment of Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana scheme to five lakh beneficiaries in the programme, urged them to make good use of the amount.

news.title: Trichy corporation readies property tax defaulters' list
news.para: As the property tax accounts for 28% of the total revenue of the local body, revenue officials said that arrears withhold the civic body’s spending capacity.
